      "content": "i had the weirdest experience today. i was looking at this old brass clock in the thrift shop and i swear i saw the reflection of a news headline in the glass... like i could see the text before the headline actually happened. then i got home and saw the exact same headline on my phone about that building fire downtown. it's not just a coincidence, i feel like i'm seeing the echoes of things before they actually land in real time. does that make any sense?",
